|YK0SYNTAX
======
|YKBset|YK0
|YKBset list|YK0
|YKBset <option> <value>|YK0

DESCRIPTION
===========
The set command lets you view and change saved character options.

Use |YKBset|YK0 or |YKBset list|YK0 to show your current settings.
Use |YKBset <option> <value>|YK0 to change one setting.

OPTIONS
======
  |YKBallow <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether your session may be snooped.

  |YKBanonymous <off|on>|YK0
    Hides player specifics from finger and who.

  |YKBautoexits <off|on>|YK0
    Sets whether detailed exit information is shown.

  |YKBautoburn <off|on>|YK0
    Uses a carried corpse burner to run |YKBburn corpse|YK0 after autorefine or
    autosell, autoloot, and autogold have finished processing an NPC corpse.
    This uses the normal burn command and destroys anything left inside.

  |YKBautogold <off|on>|YK0
    Automatically takes gold from NPC corpses you kill.

  |YKBautolevel <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether non-remort characters automatically spend
    experience to gain levels.

  |YKBautoloot <off|on>|YK0
    Automatically takes gettable loot from NPC corpses you kill.

  |YKBautorefine <off|on>|YK0
    Permanently converts ordinary refinery-eligible equipment from NPCs you
    kill into saved profession materials. This uses the same yields as the
    Refinery and disables autosell. Magical, unique, limited, customized,
    scripted, and otherwise protected items remain in the corpse, exactly
    as with autosell. Leave it off if you want to inspect equipment drops
    before deciding what to do with them.

  |YKBautosell <off|on>|YK0
    Uses a carried corpse burner to sell ordinary weapons and armour from
    NPC corpses directly to Taylor. His normal Charisma and reputation
    pricing applies, followed by a 10 percent handling charge. Magical,
    unique, limited, customized, scripted, and otherwise protected items
    remain in the corpse. Enabling this disables autorefine.

  |YKBbrief <off|on>|YK0
    Sets the amount of room descriptions that are shown.

  |YKBcolorblock <off|on>|YK0
    Blocks other players' custom color codes in channel messages.

  |YKBcombatbrief-damage <off|on>|YK0
    Shows damage numbers at the end of combat messages.

  |YKBcombatbrief-hit <off|on>|YK0
    Hides misses and dodges from combat messages.

  |YKBcombatbrief-self <off|on>|YK0
    Shows only attacks by or on you.

  |YKBcombatbrief-short <off|on>|YK0
    Uses shorter combat messages.

  |YKBemail <email@domain.com>|YK0
    Sets your current e-mail address.

  |YKBforwarding <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether MUD mail is forwarded to your e-mail address.

  |YKBgiphy <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether shared GIFs auto-open in Darkflow.

  |YKBitemdetail <off|on>|YK0
    Shows an item's AC or WC in its description.

  |YKBlanguage <language>|YK0
    Sets your default language to speak with.

  |YKBmonitor <off|on|bar>|YK0
    Sets how your remaining HP/SP are shown.

  |YKBmorelen <1-75>|YK0
    Sets the more paging length.

  |YKBnotifylooks <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether you are notified when others look at you.

  |YKBnpcdetail <off|on>|YK0
    Shows a level and indicator on non-player characters.

  |YKBpavail <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether you are marked as looking for a party.

  |YKBpk <off|on>|YK0
    Sets your player killing flag.

  |YKBprompt <string>|YK0
    Sets the string used as your prompt.
    Wizards can use:
      %d  current working directory
      %i  current invis level
      %wi whoinvis indicator
      %f  fakeidle indicator
      %e  environment, D/P for dev/prod

  |YKBrealm <off|on>|YK0
    Newbie-only setting for whether you start in the realm where you quit.

  |YKBscreenreader <off|on>|YK0
    Enables output adjustments for screenreader users.

  |YKBsharedvideo <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether shared YouTube videos auto-open in Darkflow.

  |YKBshowmultis <off|on|main>|YK0
    Controls whether finger shows your registered multies, only your main
    character, or neither.

  |YKBteapotspam <off|on>|YK0
    Controls whether your enchanted teapot emits idle room chatter.

  |YKBterm <none|ansi|modern|vt100|vt52>|YK0
    Sets which terminal type you are using to connect.

  |YKBtimestamps <off|on>|YK0
    Sets timestamps on or off when viewing channel histories.

  |YKBvirginears <off|on>|YK0
    Turns your personal profanity filter on or off.

  |YKBvisemail <off|on>|YK0
    Allows your e-mail address to be seen by others.

  |YKBwebsite <http://...>|YK0
    Adds your web page address to your finger info.

  |YKBwimpy <0-100>|YK0
    Sets the HP percentage where you automatically run away.

  |YKBwimpycmd <command|none>|YK0
    Sets the command attempted when you wimpy, or clears it with none.

